@Honny1 to clarify on the error content point: when buildah opens a non-Containerfile as the dockerfile (e.g., a host file containing `mytoken123`), the build error stream does reflect parsed line content:

error building at STEP "MYTOKEN123": ...

buildah uppercases the line (treating it as an instruction keyword), but the original content is recoverable. this is what the attached PoC demonstrates end-to-end.

@inknos updating the docs to match the actual behavior is also reasonable. the current compat swagger doc describes `dockerfile` as "path within the build context"(`pkg/api/server/register_images.go:507`), so if the intended behavior is to allow host-absolute paths and context escapes, the docs should say so explicitly.

either approach works — code fix (PR #28072) or docs clarification. happy to close this if neither is wanted.
